  "type": "spr",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">The table above shows the coordinates of three points on a line in the <span class=\"italic \">xy</span>-plane, where <span class=\"italic\">k</span> and <span class=\"italic\">n</span> are constants. If the slope of the line is 2, what is the value of <span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k plus n\"></span>&nbsp;</span>?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [],
  "keys": [],
  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is 30. The slope of a line can be found by using the slope formula, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator y sub 2 minus y sub 1, and denominator x sub 2 minus x sub 1, end fraction\"></span>. It&rsquo;s given that the slope of the line is 2; therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator y sub 2 minus y sub 1, and denominator x sub 2 minus x sub 1, end fraction, equals 2\"></span>. According to the table, the points <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"with coordinates 3 comma 7\"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"with coordinates k comma 11\"></span> lie on the line. Substituting the coordinates of these points into the equation gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator 11 minus 7, and denominator k minus 3, end fraction, equals 2\"></span>. Multiplying both sides of this equation by <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k minus 3 \"></span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"11 minus 7, equals, 2 times, open parenthesis, k minus 3, close parenthesis\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"11 minus 7, equals, 2 k minus 6\"></span>. Solving for <span class=\"italic\">k</span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k equals 5\"></span>. According to the table, the points <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"with coordinates 3 comma 7\"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"with coordinates 12 comma n\"></span> also lie on the line. Substituting the coordinates of these points into <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator y sub 2 minus y sub 1, and denominator x sub 2 minus x sub 1, end fraction, equals 2 \"></span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator n minus 7, and denominator 12 minus 3, end fraction, equals 2\"></span>. Solving for <span class=\"italic\">n</span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"n equals 25\"></span>. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"k plus n, equals, 5 plus 25\"></span>, or 30.</p>\n",
